# UNIT App — Cursor Context

## What This App Is
Delivery driver tool for Speed X drivers. Scan packages → assign to geographic zones
→ optimize route → sequential numbered navigation. Built for Director X's daily routes.
Director X drives a 2018 Jeep Grand Cherokee (suv_midsize).

## Live URL
https://unit-6gxn.onrender.com

## Stack
- Backend: Python / Flask
- Database: SQLite
- AI Vision: Anthropic Claude Vision (package scanning / address extraction)
- Routing: OSRM
- Maps: Leaflet.js
- Frontend: HTML/CSS/JS (served via Flask templates)

## Project Structure
- app.py — main Flask app, all routes and logic
- templates/ — HTML templates (scan, map, route views)
- static/ — CSS, JS, assets
- database.db — SQLite (packages, addresses, routes, zone intel)
- start.sh — local run script

## Vehicle Zones (Jeep Grand Cherokee — suv_midsize)
Load order (deepest first):
1. Cargo Back — furthest deliveries, loaded first
2. Cargo Middle
3. Cargo Liftgate
4. Back Seat R / M / L
5. Front Passenger — closest deliveries, loaded last

## Current Architecture (Being Rebuilt)
### What exists:
- Screenshot import flow (Claude Vision extracts addresses from Speed X screenshots)
- Live barcode scanning
- Zone assignment (currently count-based — being replaced)
- OSRM route optimization
- Leaflet map with zone color markers

### What is being replaced / added:
- COUNT-BASED zone balancing → REMOVED (this caused re-sorting chaos)
- Replacing with: K-MEANS GEOGRAPHIC CLUSTERING (zones based on address location, not count)
- Adding: ZIP code sector visualization (color-coded sectors on map)
- Adding: Address intelligence database (learns zones from route history)
- Adding: Loading plan screen (shown before physical sorting begins)

## Core Rules — DO NOT VIOLATE
1. Packages are touched ONCE — during loading. Never re-sorted.
2. Scanning phase = data collection only. No physical sorting signals during scan.
3. K-means runs ONCE after all packages are scanned and Optimize is hit.
4. Sectors are LOCKED after optimize. No rebalancing after that point.
5. Late additions → appended to end of route. No re-clustering.
6. Sector count = max 5 (matches vehicle zone count).
7. Loading plan screen must show before any sorting begins (which sector → which car zone).

## The Correct Flow
PHASE 1 — SCAN: Scan all packages. Dots appear on map (visual only). No sorting yet.
PHASE 2 — OPTIMIZE: K-means runs on complete dataset. Sectors finalized + locked.
           Route numbered 1→end. Loading plan generated.
PHASE 3 — SORT ONCE: Follow loading plan. One pass. Done.
PHASE 4 — DRIVE: Sequential route. No backtracking.

## Address Intelligence DB (In Progress)
- Every scanned/imported address saved with: ZIP, coordinates, sector assignment, route date
- Over time: ZIP → sector mapping is learned and predicted on scan
- Apartment complexes and recurring addresses auto-recognized
- Goal: by last scan, system semi-predicts full route

## ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
## SPOKE-STYLE SCAN-TO-ROUTE — FEATURE BUILD SPEC
## ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
## Goal: replicate what makes Spoke feel instant and smooth.
## Spoke = Circuit Route Planner (rebranded). It uses:
##   - Apple Live Text (native iOS OCR) — no server call, result in <1 second
##   - Google Maps Route Optimization API — not OSRM, real TSP solver
##   - Auto-add on high confidence — no confirmation screen if read is clean
##   - Real-time ETA recalc after each delivery
##
## UNIT equivalent implementation:
##
## [1] AUTO-ADD ON HIGH CONFIDENCE (no confirmation tap)
##   - After Tesseract + address parse, score the result:
##       score = 0
##       +3 if tracking length >= 12
##       +5 if isPlausibleAddress(address) && !_isDirtyAddress(address)
##       +2 if isPlausibleName(name)
##   - If score >= 7: skip preview card entirely, auto-POST to /driver/scan/add
##     Show a green flash banner with zone assignment ("Zone B - Cargo Back")
##     instead of the preview card confirm button.
##   - If score < 7: show preview card as normal (current behavior).
##   - Add a small "Undo" button in the zone banner (5-second window) in case
##     auto-add grabbed the wrong package.
##
## [2] REPLACE OSRM WITH GOOGLE MAPS DIRECTIONS API (route optimization)
##   - In app.py, find all OSRM calls (search for "osrm" or "router.osrm.org")
##   - Replace with Google Maps Directions API:
##       endpoint: https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/directions/json
##       method: GET
##       params: origin, destination, waypoints (pipe-separated),
##               optimize:waypoints=true, key=GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY
##   - "optimize:waypoints=true" triggers Google TSP solver (same thing Spoke uses)
##   - Read GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY from env var (os.environ.get('GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY', ''))
##   - If key is missing or call fails: fall back to existing OSRM logic (no prod breakage)
##   - Return: ordered stop list, total distance (meters), total duration (seconds)
##   - Convert to miles + minutes before storing in DB
##   - Use Directions API NOT the newer Routes API (simpler, proven)
##
## [3] REAL-TIME ETA RECALC AFTER EACH DELIVERY
##   - In stop_active.html, after marking a stop complete:
##     POST to /driver/route/<id>/eta-refresh
##   - Backend: re-run Directions API from current GPS position through remaining stops
##     Return updated ETAs for all remaining stops
##   - Frontend: update ETA display without page reload (AJAX, update DOM)
##   - If offline: recalc from last known position using haversine / avg speed
##
## [4] CAMERA SCAN SPEED - REDUCE TAPS
##   - Current: tap placeholder -> tap capture -> wait for OCR -> see preview
##   - Target: camera opens -> frame auto-detects label -> captures automatically
##   - Implement: after camera stream starts, run Tesseract.js on a frame every 1.5s
##     When OCR score >= 7, auto-capture (stop loop, process the frame)
##     Show a "Scanning..." pulse indicator while the loop is running
##   - Keep "Manual Capture" button as fallback (still shows capture-btn)
##   - Feels like Spoke's Live Text: point camera -> done
##
## [5] ZONE FLASH BANNER (after auto-add)
##   - Full-width colored banner slides in from top, auto-dismisses in 4s
##   - Shows: zone emoji + zone letter + vehicle spot name + sticker number
##     Example: "Zone B -> Back Seat Right | #12 | Undo"
##   - Color matches zone color from clustering
##   - Haptic: navigator.vibrate(60) on auto-add success
##
## IMPLEMENTATION ORDER:
##   Step 1 - Auto-add on high confidence (biggest UX gain, no API key needed)
##   Step 2 - Camera auto-capture loop (makes scan feel like Live Text)
##   Step 3 - Zone flash banner (ties steps 1+2 together visually)
##   Step 4 - Google Maps routing swap (needs GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY in env)
##   Step 5 - Real-time ETA recalc (depends on Step 4)
##
## FILES TO TOUCH:
##   - templates/scan.html   -> Steps 1, 2, 3 (JS changes only)
##   - app.py                -> Step 4 (routing swap) + Step 5 (eta-refresh endpoint)
##   - render.yaml           -> add GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY env var placeholder
##
## DO NOT BREAK:
##   - Existing preview card flow (still needed when score < 7)
##   - Import-first panel (screenshot import still works)
##   - Zone lock / optimize flow
##   - Vehicle zone assignments
##   - OSRM fallback (must stay active when Google key not set)
