## ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
## SPEED X POD (PROOF OF DELIVERY) - 3-PHOTO CAPTURE FLOW
## ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
##
## Speed X requires EXACTLY 3 photos before a delivery can be marked complete.
## Confirmed from real delivery photos (Director X's actual workflow):
##
##   PHOTO 1 - Package label close-up
##             Tracking number must be clearly visible (e.g. SPXDTW036626060..)
##             Driver holds the package and shoots the label
##
##   PHOTO 2 - Package at the door, wide shot
##             Shows full scene: package placed at door, house/building visible
##             Address numbers should be readable in frame
##
##   PHOTO 3 - Address numbers close-up
##             Tight shot of the physical house/unit number on the building
##             Confirms the correct address was delivered to
##
## BUILD THIS INTO stop_active.html:
##
##   1. Replace the "Mark Delivered" button with a 3-step photo stepper
##   2. Show clear progress: Step 1 of 3 / Step 2 of 3 / Step 3 of 3
##   3. Each step shows a large prompt card with icon + instruction:
##        Step 1: camera icon + "Shoot the package label - tracking number visible"
##        Step 2: door icon  + "Package at the door - show full placement + house"
##        Step 3: numbers icon + "Close-up of address numbers on the building"
##   4. Tap prompt -> <input type=file accept=image/* capture=environment> fires
##      (forces rear camera directly, no gallery)
##   5. After each shot: thumbnail preview with RETAKE and USE PHOTO buttons
##   6. After all 3 confirmed: green "Mark Delivered" button activates
##   7. On Mark Delivered:
##      - Save all 3 photos to device camera roll (download via JS blob URL)
##      - Store base64 thumbnails in DB against the stop (pod_photo_1/2/3 columns)
##      - POST to /driver/stop/<id>/deliver with photo data
##      - Redirect to next stop
##
## BACKEND CHANGES (app.py):
##   - ALTER TABLE stops ADD COLUMN pod_photo_1 TEXT (base64 thumbnail)
##   - ALTER TABLE stops ADD COLUMN pod_photo_2 TEXT
##   - ALTER TABLE stops ADD COLUMN pod_photo_3 TEXT
##   - ALTER TABLE stops ADD COLUMN pod_captured_at TEXT
##   - /driver/stop/<id>/deliver endpoint: accept pod photos in POST body
##   - /driver/stop/<id>/pod GET: return the 3 thumbnails for review
##
## ROUTE LOG VIEW:
##   - In route_log.html or route_detail.html, show POD thumbnails per stop
##   - Driver can review all 3 photos per stop before batch uploading to Speed X
##   - Display in delivery order so Speed X upload is systematic
##
## END OF DAY WORKFLOW (no Speed X API needed):
##   - All 3 photos auto-downloaded to camera roll during delivery
##   - Driver opens Speed X once at end of day
##   - Selects photos from camera roll in order (they are timestamped + GPS tagged)
##   - UNIT route log confirms which photos go to which stop
##
## GRACEFUL DEGRADATION:
##   - If camera permission denied: show "Allow camera in Settings" message
##     but also offer "Skip Photos" escape hatch (for edge cases)
##   - Never block marking a stop delivered permanently
##   - If photo storage fails: still mark delivered, log the error
##
## DO NOT CHANGE:
##   - Existing failed/undo stop logic
##   - En-route flow or GPS tracking
##   - SMS notification timing
